Unilever to Invest 50 Million Euros in Russian Sauce Production

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-10-17T10:20:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/unilever-to-invest-50-million-euros-in-russian-sauce-production.html
Unilever, the world’s second-largest
consumer-goods company, said it will invest about 50 million
euros ($69 million) in production of sauces in  Russia ’s central
region of Tula by the end of 2014.  Unilever agreed with government authorities to expand sauce
production in Tula, the London and Rotterdam-based company said
in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
